			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It's me again.  In reference to the last post I made let me expound for the rest of you.  First of all, please pardon my horrendous spelling. I was in a bit of a hurry and wanted to amke sure the gist of my message got through.  Now, about the spells.  I am an Eudite wizard of thde 12th level, about to become 13th.  In my experience, these two spells - Sphere of Light at 4th and Halo of Light at 8th - have compensated very nicely for a lack of nightvision.  Granted, they don't do much in Toxxulia Forest but then waht does :). However, in the more normal zones, like Qeynos and BlackBurrow, they are both excellent resources.  I always make sure to have a Light Halo on in BB not only because it sheds light equal to a greater lightstone but because it provides one ac better than a cloth cap.  Cloth caps are a head slot item and so are Haloes.  I looked at my AC when switching between the two and lo and behold, one more point of armor between me and those nasty gnolls.  Anyway, I think this sums up my argument pretty well.  Thank you for your time.
				</font>
