	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I hope this hasn't already been posted; I'm NOT going to read 15 pages of posts to find out.<BR>
There is an extremely easy quest to do if you're new in Erud that will get you to lvl 5 VERY quickly:<BR>
Do the Poisoned Erud's tonic quest. Each iteration will cost you about 1.2 gold and take maybe 20 minutes<BR>
of your time. (Less after lvl 4 when you get gate) At first the experience gained is quite impressive. <BR>
After lvl 5 the experience isn't really worth it anymore, but it can get you from lvl 1 to 4 in maybe 3 hours.<BR>
 Instructions:<BR>
1) - Buy an &quot;Innoruuk's Kiss of Death&quot; drink at Blue Hawk.<BR>
2) - Give it to Sinnkin in the library. She will give you back an Erud's Tonic. (and exp!)<BR>
3) - Give the Erud's Tonic to Nolusia Finharn at the Inn. She will give you back a poisoned Erud's Tonic, but it won't say &quot;poisoned&quot;.<BR>
4) - Go back to the Blue Hawk and buy ANOTHER &quot;Innoruuk's Kiss of Death&quot;. (and exp!)<BR>
5) - Exchange this second drink for ANOTHER Erud's Tonic from Sinnkin. (more exp!)<BR>
  NOTE - You have to keep these straight: The non-poisoned one is LORE NO DROP, and the poisoned one is just LORE.<BR>
6) - Take the boat to Qeynos and go to North Qeynos.<BR>
7) - Find Moodoro (an erudite) at Crow's inn. He'll be either out in front or inside.<BR>
8) - Give the NON-poisoned Erud's tonic to Moodoro. (you'll get exp and a bit of copper)<BR>
9) - Inside, give the poisoned Erud's tonic to a halfling named Flynn. (MUCHO exp!) You'll then have the label for the bottle in your inventory.<BR>
10) - Go back to Erud.<BR>
11) - Give the label to Nolusia. You'll get another BIG burst of experience, and a cheap weapon you can sell for about a gold or so.<BR>
<BR>
 SHORT VERSION:<BR>
Just keep giving Erud's tonics to Nolusia. It's very very fast, but you'll run out of money fairly quickly too.<BR>
NOTE: Nolusia appears SIMULTANEOUSLY in the palace and at the inn. Ignore the palace one.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
